<section id="story" class="flex flex-col md:flex-row w-full">
  <!-- Left – founder portrait -->
  <div class="w-full md:w-55 relative overflow-hidden flex items-center" style="min-height: 360px; aspect-ratio: 3/4;">
    {%- if section.settings.founder_image != blank -%}
      <img
        src="{{ section.settings.founder_image | image_url: width: 1200 }}"
        alt="Gurkamal, Founder of BaseCode"
        width="848" height="1264" loading="lazy"
        class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full"
        style="object-fit: cover; object-position: top;">
    {%- else -%}
      <div class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, #162a1e, #1C2E23);"></div>
    {%- endif -%}
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(28,46,35,0.80), transparent);"></div>
    <div class="relative px-10 md:px-20 py-20 mt-auto" style="z-index: 2;">
      <p class="font-mono-spec text-11 uppercase mb-6" style="color: rgba(196,120,58,0.60); letter-spacing: 0.2em;">
        03 — Founder
      </p>
      <p class="font-heading text-14 font-medium mb-2" style="color: rgba(245,242,236,0.50);">
        Gurkamal
      </p>
      <p class="font-heading text-13 font-light" style="color: rgba(245,242,236,0.35); line-height: 1.7;">
        Founder & Formulation Researcher · BaseCode Health
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Right – manifesto -->
  <div class="w-full md:w-45 px-8 md:px-20 py-16 md:py-20 reveal-hidden" style="background: #F5F2EC;">
    <p class="font-display italic mb-10" style="color: #1C2E23; font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.3;">
      "Government taught me how systems break down. BaseCode is how I fix one."
    </p>

    <div class="font-heading text-16 md:text-17 font-light space-y-6" style="color: #4A5550; line-height: 1.9;">
      <p>
        I grew up eating real food. Not health food. Real food — fermented, slow-cooked, made from scratch every night. I didn't think about it then. It was just how we ate. I didn't understand what that food was doing for my biology until I stopped having it.
      </p>
      <p>
        University changed everything. Fast food. Late nights. Stress that never turned off. Within a year, my digestion was different. My energy was different. My focus was different. I was doing everything the wellness industry told me to do — supplements, routines, optimization — and nothing worked.
      </p>
      <p>
        When I started reading the research, I understood why. Most probiotic bacteria don't survive stomach acid. The number on the bottle — 10 billion, 30 billion, 50 billion — is measured at manufacture, not at delivery. Without acid protection, you're paying for a label, not for results.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then I found MAKTREK — a marine polysaccharide shield that protects bacteria through gastric transit. Pair that with a prebiotic that feeds them on arrival, and you have something that actually works. Not a marketing claim. A delivery system.
      </p>
      <p>
        The deeper I went, the clearer the picture got. The HELIUS study — 2,084 people, 6 population groups — showed that biology determines microbiome composition more than diet, age, or lifestyle. Sonnenburg's work proved that Western diets are systematically extinguishing beneficial bacterial species. McEwen's allostatic load research showed that chronic stress physically rewires biological systems. The modern Western environment is taxing human biology in ways we've never seen before — and the supplement industry is still selling generic solutions to a systemic problem.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am a wrestler and an avid lifter. I think about my body for a living. When my system is underperforming, I find out why. The science is published. The biological tax is real. Nobody built a clinical-grade protocol to address it. So I built BaseCode.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="font-display italic mt-8 mb-8 pl-6" style="color: #C4783A; border-left: 3px solid #C4783A; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.4;">
      "I have a seven-month-old daughter. There are things I want to understand about my own biology before they become questions about hers."
    </p>

    <p class="font-display italic mt-10 mb-6" style="color: #C4783A; font-size: 18px;">
      "Your biology is paying a tax.<br>
      BaseCode is the down-regulation."
    </p>

    <p class="font-mono-spec text-13 mb-8" style="color: #8A9490;">
      — Gurkamal, Founder · BaseCode
    </p>

    <a href="/pages/free-report" class="inline-block font-heading text-15 font-medium py-3 transition hover:underline" style="color: #C4783A;">
      Read the research that started it all →
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Founder",
  "class": "founder-section",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "image_picker", "id": "founder_image", "label": "Founder Photo" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
